g3connectState.name: g3connectState
g3connectState.description: The current state of the switch connection; this object cat be set to 'off' to disable the connection and can be set to 'init' to re-initialize the connection. It can also be set to 'idle', if the g3connectType is 'dynamic', to put turn off the connection until a request is received.

g3connectTimeUp.name: g3connectTimeUp
g3connectTimeUp.description: The elapsed time since the connection was established

g3connectTimeUnused.name: g3connectTimeUnused
g3connectTimeUnused.description: The elapsed time since the connection was last used

g3connectRequests.name: g3connectRequests
g3connectRequests.description: The number of switch data requests

g3connectResponses.name: g3connectResponses
g3connectResponses.description: The number of switch data responses

g3connectErrors.name: g3connectErrors
g3connectErrors.description: The number of switch connection errors

g3connectQueued.name: g3connectQueued
g3connectQueued.description: The number switch requests in the input queue

g3connectDelay.name: g3connectDelay
g3connectDelay.description: The expected delay in retrieving switch data

g3connectAlarmForward.name: g3connectAlarmForward
g3connectAlarmForward.description: This object serves as a flag to indicate if a failure has occured in forwarding alarms received from the switch on to another destination.

g3connectTimeReset.name: g3connectTimeReset
g3connectTimeReset.description: The elapsed time since the connection counters were last reset. Setting this object to zero will reset the counters.

g3connectType.name: g3connectType
g3connectType.description: The type of the switch connection; it is either 'static' which will stay up continuously or 'dynamic' which will be dropped after the connection is idle for a period of time.

g3connectTimeout.name: g3connectTimeout
g3connectTimeout.description: The number of idle minutes a 'dynamic' connection will stay connected before being dropped. For a 'static' connection this field is not applicable an contains a value of zero

g3vintageTage.name: g3vintageTage
g3vintageTage.description: The number of timeticks since the vintage data was last extracted from the switch by the G3 Proxy Agent. This object along with the g3vintageTintvl object allows the Network Manager to determine the validity of the vintage data in the cache and to control when the proxy agent extracts the vintage data from the switch.

g3vintageTintvl.name: g3vintageTintvl
g3vintageTintvl.description: An object containing the interval for which the vintage data extracted from the switch is considered valid by the proxy agent. When a GET or GET-NEXT request for vintage objects is received by the agent it uses the g3vintageTage and g3vintageTintvl objects to determine whether it should refresh the cached vintage data. If g3vintageTstmp + g3vintageTintvl is less than the current value of the sysUpTime object then the agent refreshes the vintage data cache. In either case it responds to the requests it receives with the data it currently has in the cache.

g3vintageTdelay.name: g3vintageTdelay
g3vintageTdelay.description: An object containing the delay encountered in updating the cached data

g3vintageTretrieve.name: g3vintageTretrieve
g3vintageTretrieve.description: An INTEGER object containing a flag that is 'update' if the cached data is being retrieved and otherwise 'current'. This object may be set to 'update' to force a refresh of the cache.

g3vintageSpeArelease.name: g3vintageSpeArelease
g3vintageSpeArelease.description: A DisplayString Object that contains the release number for SPE A.

g3vintageSpeBrelease.name: g3vintageSpeBrelease
g3vintageSpeBrelease.description: A DisplayString Object that contains the release number for SPE B.

g3vintageCurMemory.name: g3vintageCurMemory
g3vintageCurMemory.description: A DisplayString Object that contains the current memory configuration.

g3vintageSpeAupID.name: g3vintageSpeAupID
g3vintageSpeAupID.description: A DisplayString Object that contains the update identifier for SPE A.

g3vintageSpeBupID.name: g3vintageSpeBupID
g3vintageSpeBupID.description: A DisplayString Object that contains the update identifier for SPE B.

g3vintageSpeAupState1.name: g3vintageSpeAupState1
g3vintageSpeAupState1.description: A DisplayString Object that contains the first part of the update state for SPE A.

g3vintageSpeBupState1.name: g3vintageSpeBupState1
g3vintageSpeBupState1.description: A DisplayString Object that contains the first part of the update state for SPE B.

g3vintageSpeAupState2.name: g3vintageSpeAupState2
g3vintageSpeAupState2.description: A DisplayString Object that contains the second part of the update state for SPE A.

g3vintageSpeBupState2.name: g3vintageSpeBupState2
g3vintageSpeBupState2.description: A DisplayString Object that contains the second part of the update state for SPE B.

g3vintageVSPacketBus.name: g3vintageVSPacketBus
g3vintageVSPacketBus.description: A DisplayString Object that contains the a flag indicating whether packet bus is available on a G3vs system.

g3vintageOfferCategory.name: g3vintageOfferCategory
g3vintageOfferCategory.description: A DisplayString Object that contains the current Offer Category ('A', 'B', or '?').

g3vintageATMPnc.name: g3vintageATMPnc
g3vintageATMPnc.description: A DisplayString Object that contains the current ATM PNC Customer Option ('y', or 'n').

g3vintageProductID.name: g3vintageProductID
g3vintageProductID.description: A DisplayString Object that contains the Product Identification number for the Definity switch.

g3vintageOSSNumber1.name: g3vintageOSSNumber1
g3vintageOSSNumber1.description: A DisplayString Object that contains the first OSS telephone number.

g3vintageAbbAlmRep1.name: g3vintageAbbAlmRep1
g3vintageAbbAlmRep1.description: A DisplayString Object that contains the Abbreviated Alarm Report for the first OSS Number ('y' or 'n').

g3vintageOSSNumber2.name: g3vintageOSSNumber2
g3vintageOSSNumber2.description: A DisplayString Object that contains the second OSS telephone number.

g3vintageAbbAlmRep2.name: g3vintageAbbAlmRep2
g3vintageAbbAlmRep2.description: A DisplayString Object that contains the Abbreviated Alarm Report for the second OSS Number ('y' or 'n').

g3vintageAOActivate.name: g3vintageAOActivate
g3vintageAOActivate.description: A DisplayString Object that contains Alarm Origination Activation status ('y' or 'n').

g3vintageCANotify.name: g3vintageCANotify
g3vintageCANotify.description: A DisplayString Object that contains Cleared Alarm Notification status ('y' or 'n').

g3vintageResNotify.name: g3vintageResNotify
g3vintageResNotify.description: A DisplayString Object that contains Restart Notification status ('y' or 'n').

g3vintagePbxID.name: g3vintagePbxID
g3vintagePbxID.description: An INTEGER Object containing the Local Node Number for pre R11

g3vintageACAFlag.name: g3vintageACAFlag
g3vintageACAFlag.description: A DisplayString Object that contains the current ACA Enabled Option ('y', or 'n').

g3vintageIPAddress1.name: g3vintageIPAddress1
g3vintageIPAddress1.description: An object that contains the first octet of IP address

g3vintageIPAddress2.name: g3vintageIPAddress2
g3vintageIPAddress2.description: An object that contains the second octet of IP address

g3vintageIPAddress3.name: g3vintageIPAddress3
g3vintageIPAddress3.description: An object that contains the third octet of IP address

g3vintageIPAddress4.name: g3vintageIPAddress4
g3vintageIPAddress4.description: An object that contains the fourth octet of IP address

g3vintageLocalNodeNbr.name: g3vintageLocalNodeNbr
g3vintageLocalNodeNbr.description: An INTEGER Object containing the Local Node Number on R11 and beyond

g3vintageIPStaReg.name: g3vintageIPStaReg
g3vintageIPStaReg.description: An object that contains the number of current registered IP stations on the media server.

g3vintageIPStaAvail.name: g3vintageIPStaAvail
g3vintageIPStaAvail.description: An object that contains the number of concurrent IP stations still available on the media server.

g3vintageIPStaLimit.name: g3vintageIPStaLimit
g3vintageIPStaLimit.description: An object that contains the total system limit of concurrent IP stations on the media server.

g3vintageIPAttdReg.name: g3vintageIPAttdReg
g3vintageIPAttdReg.description: An object that contains the number of current registered IP attendant consoles on the media server.

g3vintageIPAttdAvail.name: g3vintageIPAttdAvail
g3vintageIPAttdAvail.description: An object that contains the number of concurrent IP attendant consoles still available on the media server.

g3vintageIPAttdLimit.name: g3vintageIPAttdLimit
g3vintageIPAttdLimit.description: An object that contains the total system limit of concurrent IP attendant consoles on the media server.

g3vintageRemoteOffReg.name: g3vintageRemoteOffReg
g3vintageRemoteOffReg.description: An object that contains the number of current registered remote office stations on the media server.

g3vintageRemoteOffAvail.name: g3vintageRemoteOffAvail
g3vintageRemoteOffAvail.description: An object that contains the number of concurrent remote office stations still available on the media server.

g3vintageRemoteOffLimit.name: g3vintageRemoteOffLimit
g3vintageRemoteOffLimit.description: An object that contains the total system limit of concurrent remote office stations on the media server.

g3configTintvl.description: An object containing the interval for which the configuration data extracted from the switch is considered valid by the proxy agent. In either case it responds to the requests it receives with the data it currently has in the cache.

g3configTdelay.name: g3configTdelay
g3configTdelay.description: An object containing the delay encountered in updating the cached data

g3configTcount.name: g3configTcount
g3configTcount.description: A Gauge object containing the number of data records in the cache.

g3configEntry.name: g3configEntry
g3configEntry.description: A g3config entry containing objects of the g3config information sent by the switch.

g3configBoardNum.name: g3configBoardNum
g3configBoardNum.description: A DisplayString Object that uniquely identifies a board based on its location in the system. The syntax for the Board Number is as follows: cabinet(01-44):carrier(A-E):slot(01-20).

g3configIndex.name: g3configIndex
g3configIndex.description: An INTEGER object containing an index numbering the config entry for the board specified in BoardNum. This object along with BoardNum will serve as the instance identifier for boardEntry.

g3configBoardType.name: g3configBoardType
g3configBoardType.description: A DisplayString Object that contains a text description of the type of board.

g3configCode.name: g3configCode
g3configCode.description: A DisplayString Object that contains the code that defines the type of board.

g3configSuffix.name: g3configSuffix
g3configSuffix.description: A DisplayString Object that contains the suffix to the code (object configCode) that defines the type of board.

g3configVintage.name: g3configVintage
g3configVintage.description: An DisplayString Object that contains the vintage of the board.

g3configPort1.name: g3configPort1
g3configPort1.description: A DisplayString Object that specifies the assignment of the port. A string representing an integer identical to the port number indicates that the port is assigned. The string (u) indicates that the port is unassigned. The string (t) indicates that the port is assigned via the TTI feature. A null string indicates that the port does not exist on that board.

g3alarmsTage.description: The number of timeticks since the alarm data was last extracted from the switch by the G3 Proxy Agent. This object along with the g3alarmsTintvl object allows the Network Manager to determine the validity of the alarm data in the cache and to control when the proxy agent extracts the alarm data from the switch.

g3alarmsTintvl.name: g3alarmsTintvl
g3alarmsTintvl.description: An object containing the interval for which the alarm data extracted from the switch is considered valid by the proxy agent. When a GET or GET-NEXT request for alarm objects is received by the agent it uses the g3alarmsTage and g3alarmsTintvl objects to determine whether it should refresh the cached alarmsTable. If g3alarmsTstmp + g3alarmsTintvl is less than the current value of the sysUpTime object then the agent refreshes the alarmsTable cache. In either case it responds to the requests it receives with the data it currently has in the cache.

g3alarmsTdelay.name: g3alarmsTdelay
g3alarmsTdelay.description: An object containing the delay encountered in updating the cached data

g3alarmsTretrieve.name: g3alarmsTretrieve
g3alarmsTretrieve.description: An INTEGER object containing a flag that is 'update' if the cached data is being retrieved and otherwise 'current'. This object may be set to 'update' to force a refresh of the cache.

g3alarmsTcount.name: g3alarmsTcount
g3alarmsTcount.description: A Gauge object containing the number of data records in the cache.

g3alarmsEntry.name: g3alarmsEntry
g3alarmsEntry.description: A g3alarms entry containing objects of the g3alarms information sent by the switch.

g3alarmsPort.name: g3alarmsPort
g3alarmsPort.description: A DisplayString Object that uniquely identifies a port based on its location in the system. The syntax for the Port number is as follows: cabinet(01-44):carrier(A-E):slot(01-20):port(01-32). This object along with alIndex will serve as the instance identifier for alarmsEntry.

g3alarmsIndex.name: g3alarmsIndex
g3alarmsIndex.description: An INTEGER object containing an index numbering the alarm entry for the port specified in alarmsPort. This object along with alarmsPort will serve as the instance identifier for alarmsEntry.

g3alarmsMaintName.name: g3alarmsMaintName
g3alarmsMaintName.description: A DisplayString Object containing the Maintenance Object Name.

g3alarmsOnBrd.name: g3alarmsOnBrd
g3alarmsOnBrd.description: A DisplayString Object specifying whether or not the alarm indicates an on board fault.

g3alarmsAltName.name: g3alarmsAltName
g3alarmsAltName.description: A DisplayString Object containing the alternate name of the alarmed object. Alternate names can consist of extension numbers, trunk group numbers or other identifying data.

g3alarmsAlarmType.name: g3alarmsAlarmType
g3alarmsAlarmType.description: A DisplayString Object specifying the alarm type (or severity).

g3alarmsSvcState.name: g3alarmsSvcState
g3alarmsSvcState.description: A DisplayString Object specifying the service state of the alarmed object. Service States can be IN or OUT {any others?}.

g3alarmsAck.name: g3alarmsAck
g3alarmsAck.description: A DisplayString Object indicating whether or not the alarm has been acknowledged by the alarm receiver.

g3alarmsMonthAlrmd.name: g3alarmsMonthAlrmd
g3alarmsMonthAlrmd.description: A DisplayString Object containing the month the alarm was created.

g3alarmsDayAlrmd.name: g3alarmsDayAlrmd
g3alarmsDayAlrmd.description: A DisplayString Object containing the day the alarm was created.

g3alarmsHourAlrmd.name: g3alarmsHourAlrmd
g3alarmsHourAlrmd.description: A DisplayString Object containing the hour the alarm was created.

g3alarmsMinAlrmd.name: g3alarmsMinAlrmd
g3alarmsMinAlrmd.description: A DisplayString Object containing the minute the alarm was created.

g3alarmsMonthRslvd.name: g3alarmsMonthRslvd
g3alarmsMonthRslvd.description: A DisplayString Object containing the month the alarm was resolved. This object will always contain the value (00) because this table only contains open alarms. This object is included in the table for future enhancements and for completeness.

g3alarmsDayRslvd.name: g3alarmsDayRslvd
g3alarmsDayRslvd.description: A DisplayString Object containing the day the alarm was resolved. This object will always contain the value (00) because this table only contains open alarms. This object is included in the table for future enhancements and for completeness.

g3alarmsHourRslvd.name: g3alarmsHourRslvd
g3alarmsHourRslvd.description: A DisplayString Object containing the hour the alarm was resolved. This object will always contain the value (00) because this table only contains open alarms. This object is included in the table for future enhancements and for completeness.

g3alarmsMinRslvd.name: g3alarmsMinRslvd
g3alarmsMinRslvd.description: A DisplayString Object containing the minute the alarm was resolved. This object will always contain the value (00) because this table only contains open alarms. This object is included in the table for future enhancements and for completeness.

g3alarmsAlarmNumber.name: g3alarmsAlarmNumber
g3alarmsAlarmNumber.description: A DisplayString Object containing the Alarm Number of the alarm. This is just a place holder for a field populated in alarm traps. Nothing is populated in this field. For traps supported by this MIB, it is populated with a unique alarm identifier of the form FPA:<filter number>:<month alarmed><day alarmed><hour alarmed>: <minute alarmed><second alarmed>:<month resolved><day resolved> <hour resolved><minute resolved><second resolved>: <alternate name field>:<new/modified flag>. The filter number field either contains the alarm filter number associated with the trap being generated or '00000' if a filter number is not applicable. The time resolved fields are populated with '0000000000', if the alarm has not been resolved. For some alarms the alternate name may not contain any information. The new/mod flag either contains an 'N' for a new alarm or a 'M' for a modified alarm. The above field format only applies to CM 3.1 and greater releases.

g3alarmsProductID.name: g3alarmsProductID
g3alarmsProductID.description: A DisplayString Object containing the Product ID of the alarm. This is just a place holder for a field populated in alarm traps. Nothing is populated in this field.

g3alarmsAck2.name: g3alarmsAck2
g3alarmsAck2.description: Another DisplayString Object indicating whether or not the alarm has been acknowledged.

g3alarmsSrcIPAddr.name: g3alarmsSrcIPAddr
g3alarmsSrcIPAddr.description: A DisplayString Object containing the IP address that is the source of a security attack. This is just a place holder for a field populated in alarm traps. Nothing is populated in this field.

g3alarmsSrcMACAddr.name: g3alarmsSrcMACAddr
g3alarmsSrcMACAddr.description: A DisplayString Object containing the IP address that is the MAC address that is the source of a security attack. This is just a place holder for a field populated in alarm traps. Nothing is populated in this field.

g3alarmsDestIPAddr.name: g3alarmsDestIPAddr
g3alarmsDestIPAddr.description: A DisplayString Object containing the IP address that is the destination of a security attack. This is just a place holder for a field populated in alarm traps. Nothing is populated in this field.

g3alarmsDestPort.name: g3alarmsDestPort
g3alarmsDestPort.description: A DisplayString Object containing the IP port that is the destination of a security attack. This is just a place holder for a field populated in alarm traps. Nothing is populated in this field.

g3alarmsProtocol.name: g3alarmsProtocol
g3alarmsProtocol.description: A DisplayString Object containing the protocol that a security attack is utilizing. This is just a place holder for a field populated in alarm traps. Nothing is populated in this field.

g3alarmsCount.name: g3alarmsCount
g3alarmsCount.description: A DisplayString Object containing the number of occurrences at the time that a trap was sent during a security attack. This is just a place holder for a field populated in alarm traps. Nothing is populated in this field.

g3alarmsIPAddress.name: g3alarmsIPAddress
g3alarmsIPAddress.description: A DisplayString Object containing the IP address of the server. This is just a place holder for a field populated in alarm traps. Nothing is populated in this field.

g3alarmsCategory.name: g3alarmsCategory
g3alarmsCategory.description: A DisplayString Object containing the the alarm category that the alarm belongs to. This is just a place holder for a field populated in alarm traps. Nothing is populated in this field.

g3alarmsErrorCodes.name: g3alarmsErrorCodes
g3alarmsErrorCodes.description: A DisplayString Object containing a list of up to 16 error codes that could have caused the alarm. Not all of the error codes may be the actually cause. This is just a place holder for a field populated in alarm traps. Nothing is populated in this field.

g3alarmsViolationType.name: g3alarmsViolationType
g3alarmsViolationType.description: A DisplayString Object containing the violation type associated with a security attack. This is just a place holder for a field populated in alarm traps. Nothing is populated in this field.

g3alarmsCode.name: g3alarmsCode
g3alarmsCode.description: A DisplayString Object containing the code associated with a security attack. This is just a place holder for a field populated in alarm traps. Nothing is populated in this field.

g3alarmsData.name: g3alarmsData
g3alarmsData.description: A DisplayString Object containing the data field associated with a security attack. This is just a place holder for a field populated in alarm traps. Nothing is populated in this field.

g3alarmsICMPType.name: g3alarmsICMPType
g3alarmsICMPType.description: A DisplayString Object containing the ICMP type associated with a security attack. This is just a place holder for a field populated in alarm traps. Nothing is populated in this field.

g3alarmsEventID.name: g3alarmsEventID
g3alarmsEventID.description: A DisplayString Object containing the event ID associated with a security attack. This is just a place holder for a field populated in alarm traps. Nothing is populated in this field.

g3alarmsStatus.name: g3alarmsStatus
g3alarmsStatus.description: A DisplayString Object containing the status associated with a security attack. This is just a place holder for a field populated in alarm traps. Nothing is populated in this field.

g3errorsErrType.name: g3errorsErrType

g3errorsAuxData.name: g3errorsAuxData
g3errorsAuxData.description: A DisplayString Object containing an auxiliary numeric code used with the errType to troubleshoot the problem.

g3errorsMonthFirst.name: g3errorsMonthFirst
g3errorsMonthFirst.description: A DisplayString Object containing the month that the error first occurred.

g3errorsDayFirst.name: g3errorsDayFirst
g3errorsDayFirst.description: A DisplayString Object containing the day that the error first occurred.

g3errorsHourFirst.name: g3errorsHourFirst
g3errorsHourFirst.description: A DisplayString Object containing the hour that the error first occurred.

g3errorsMinFirst.name: g3errorsMinFirst
g3errorsMinFirst.description: A DisplayString Object containing the minute that the error first occurred.

g3errorsMonthLast.name: g3errorsMonthLast
g3errorsMonthLast.description: A DisplayString Object containing the month that the error last occurred.

g3errorsDayLast.name: g3errorsDayLast
g3errorsDayLast.description: A DisplayString Object containing the day that the error last occurred.

g3errorsHourLast.name: g3errorsHourLast
g3errorsHourLast.description: A DisplayString Object containing the hour that the error last occurred.

g3errorsMinLast.name: g3errorsMinLast
g3errorsMinLast.description: A DisplayString Object containing the minute that the error last occurred.

g3errorsErrCnt.name: g3errorsErrCnt
g3errorsErrCnt.description: A DisplayString Object containing a numeric count of the occurrences of the error.

g3errorsErrRt.name: g3errorsErrRt
g3errorsErrRt.description: A DisplayString Object containing the error rate occurrences of the error.

g3errorsRtperHr.name: g3errorsRtperHr
g3errorsRtperHr.description: A DisplayString Object containing the error rate per hour.

g3errorsAlSt.name: g3errorsAlSt
g3errorsAlSt.description: A DisplayString Object containing the alarm state of the error.

g3errorsAck.name: g3errorsAck
g3errorsAck.description: A DisplayString Object indicating whether or not the alarm has been acknowledged by the alarm receiver.

g3healthStaticOcc.name: g3healthStaticOcc
g3healthStaticOcc.description: A Gauge object containing the proportion of the CPU which is currently dedicated to high priority items (e.g. the operating system). This percentage is rounded to the nearest integer, therefore a percentage of 0 means that the occupancy is less than one half of a percent (e.g. an occupancy of 89.6% would be displayed as 90%).

g3healthCallpOcc.name: g3healthCallpOcc
g3healthCallpOcc.description: A Gauge object containing the proportion of the CPU which is currently dedicated to call processing. This occupancy has priority over SM and IDLE occupancy categories and if needed, will take processor time away from these occupancy categories. This percentage is rounded to the nearest integer, therefore a percentage of 0 means that the occupancy is less than one half of a percent (e.g. an occupancy of 89.6% would be displayed as 90%).

g3healthSysMgmtOcc.name: g3healthSysMgmtOcc
g3healthSysMgmtOcc.description: A Gauge object containing the proportion of the CPU which is currently dedicated to system management or periodic and scheduled maintenance. Therefore, if there is a large amount of periodic or scheduled maintenance testing being performed, this occupancy percentage can be high without affecting service. This percentage is rounded to the nearest integer, therefore a percentage of 0 means that the occupancy is less than one half of a percent (e.g. an occupancy of 89.6% would be displayed as 90%).

g3healthIdleOcc.name: g3healthIdleOcc
g3healthIdleOcc.description: A Gauge object containing the proportion of the CPU which is currently available for use. This percentage is rounded to the nearest integer, therefore a percentage of 0 means that the occupancy is less than one half of a percent (e.g. an occupancy of 89.6% would be displayed as 90%).

g3healthTimeSource.description: A DisplayString Object containing the time source for the SPE (external, internal, primary, secondary, or local).

g3cabinetTage.name: g3cabinetTage
g3cabinetTage.description: The number of timeticks since the cabinet data was last extracted from the switch by the G3 Proxy Agent. This object along with the g3cabinetTintvl object allows the Network Manager to determine the validity of the error log in the cache and to control when the proxy agent extracts the cabinet data from the switch.

g3cabinetTintvl.name: g3cabinetTintvl
g3cabinetTintvl.description: An object containing the interval for which the cabinet data extracted from the switch is considered valid by the proxy agent. When a GET or GET-NEXT request for cabinet objects is received by the agent it uses the g3cabinetTage and g3cabinetTintvl objects to determine whether it should refresh the cached cabinetTable. If g3cabinetTstmp + g3cabinetTintvl is less than the current value of the sysUpTime object then the agent refreshes the cabinetTable cache. In either case it responds to the requests it receives with the data it currently has in the cache.

g3cabinetTdelay.name: g3cabinetTdelay
g3cabinetTdelay.description: An object containing the delay encountered in updating the cached data

g3cabinetTretrieve.name: g3cabinetTretrieve
g3cabinetTretrieve.description: An INTEGER object containing a flag that is 'update' if the cached data is being retrieved and otherwise 'current'. This object may be set to 'update' to force a refresh of the cache.

g3cabinetTcount.name: g3cabinetTcount
g3cabinetTcount.description: A Gauge object containing the number of data records in the cache.

g3cabinetEntry.name: g3cabinetEntry
g3cabinetEntry.description: A g3cabinet entry containing objects of the g3cabinet information sent by the switch.

g3cabtypeTage.name: g3cabtypeTage
g3cabtypeTage.description: The number of timeticks since the cabtype data was last extracted from the switch by the G3 Proxy Agent. This object along with the g3cabtypeTintvl object allows the Network Manager to determine the validity of the cabtype data in the cache and to control when the proxy agent extracts the cabtype data from the switch.

g3cabtypeTintvl.name: g3cabtypeTintvl
g3cabtypeTintvl.description: An object containing the interval for which the cabtype data extracted from the switch is considered valid by the proxy agent. When a GET or GET-NEXT request for cabtype objects is received by the agent it uses the g3cabtypeTage and g3cabtypeTintvl objects to determine whether it should refresh the cached cabtype data. If g3cabtypeTstmp + g3cabtypeTintvl is less than the current value of the sysUpTime object then the agent refreshes the cabtype data cache. In either case it responds to the requests it receives with the data it currently has in the cache.

g3cabtypeTdelay.name: g3cabtypeTdelay
g3cabtypeTdelay.description: An object containing the delay encountered in updating the cached data

g3cabtypeTretrieve.name: g3cabtypeTretrieve
g3cabtypeTretrieve.description: An INTEGER object containing a flag that is 'update' if the cached data is being retrieved and otherwise 'current'. This object may be set to 'update' to force a refresh of the cache.

g3cartypeTintvl.name: g3cartypeTintvl
g3cartypeTintvl.description: An object containing the interval for which the cartype data extracted from the switch is considered valid by the proxy agent. When a GET or GET-NEXT request for cartype objects is received by the agent it uses the g3cartypeTage and g3cartypeTintvl objects to determine whether it should refresh the cached cartype data. If g3cartypeTstmp + g3cartypeTintvl is less than the current value of the sysUpTime object then the agent refreshes the cartype data cache. In either case it responds to the requests it receives with the data it currently has in the cache.

g3siggroupTage.description: The number of timeticks since the signaling group data was extracted from the switch by the G3 Proxy Agent. g3siggroupTintvl.name: g3siggroupTintvl
g3siggroupTintvl.description: An object containing the interval for which the signaling group data extracted from the switch is considered valid by the proxy agent. When a GET or GET-NEXT request for signaling group data objects is received by the agent it uses the g3siggroupTage and g3siggroupTintvl objects to determine whether it should refresh the cached siggroupTable. If g3siggroupTstmp + g3siggroupTintvl is less than the current value of the sysUpTime object then the agent refreshes the siggroupTable cache. In either case it responds to the requests it receives with the data it currently has in the cache.

g3atmtrunkTage.name: g3atmtrunkTage
g3atmtrunkTage.description: The number of timeticks since the atm trunk data was extracted from the switch by the G3 Proxy Agent. This object along with the g3atmtrunkTintvl object allows the Network Manager to determine the validity of the atm trunk data in the cache and to control when the proxy agent extracts the atm trunk data from the switch.

g3atmtrunkTintvl.name: g3atmtrunkTintvl
g3atmtrunkTintvl.description: An object containing the interval for which the atm trunk data extracted from the switch is considered valid by the proxy agent. When a GET or GET-NEXT request for atm trunk data objects is received by the agent it uses the g3atmtrunkTage and g3atmtrunkTintvl objects to determine whether it should refresh the cached atmtrunkTable. If g3atmtrunkTstmp + g3atmtrunkTintvl is less than the current value of the sysUpTime object then the agent refreshes the atmtrunkTable cache. In either case it responds to the requests it receives with the data it currently has in the cache.

When a GET or GET-NEXT request for port network blockage objects is received by the agent it uses the g3pnblockage and g3pnblockintvl objects to determine whether it should refresh the cached pnblockTable. If g3pnblockstmp + g3pnblockintvl is less than the current value of the sysUpTime object then the agent refreshes the pnblockTable cache. In either case it responds to the requests it receives with the data it currently has in the cache.

g3pktonerecTage.name: g3pktonerecTage
g3pktonerecTage.description: The number of timeticks since the tone receiver data was last extracted from the switch by the Proxy Agent. This object along with the g3tonerecintvl object allows the Network Manager to determine the validity of the data in the cache and to control when the Proxy Agent extracts the data from the switch.

g3pktonerecTintvl.name: g3pktonerecTintvl
g3pktonerecTintvl.description: An object containing the interval for which the tone receiver data extracted from the switch is considered valid by the Proxy Agent. When a GET or GET-NEXT request for tone receiver objects is received by the agent it uses the g3tonerecage and g3tonerecintvl objects to determine whether it should refresh the cached tonerecTable. If g3tonerecstmp + g3tonerecintvl is less than the current value of the sysUpTime object then the agent refreshes the tonerecTable cache. In either case it responds to the requests it receives with the data it currently has in the cache.

g3rpatcfgTage.name: g3rpatcfgTage
g3rpatcfgTage.description: The number of timeticks since the route pattern data was last extracted from the switch by the Proxy Agent. This object along with the g3rpatcfgintvl object allows the Network Manager to determine the validity of the data in the cache and to control when the Proxy Agent extracts the data from the switch.

g3rpatcfgTintvl.name: g3rpatcfgTintvl
g3rpatcfgTintvl.description: An object containing the interval for which the route pattern data extracted from the switch is considered valid by the Proxy Agent. When a GET or GET-NEXT request for route pattern objects is received by the agent it uses the g3rpatcfgage and g3rpatcfgintvl objects to determine whether it should refresh the cached rpatcfgTable. If g3rpatcfgstmp + g3rpatcfgintvl is less than the current value of the sysUpTime object then the agent refreshes the rpatcfgTable cache. In either case it responds to the requests it receives with the data it currently has in the cache.

g3rpatcfgTdelay.description: An object containing the delay encountered in updating the cached data.

g3rpatcfgTretrieve.name: g3rpatcfgTretrieve

g3deftimeTage.name: g3deftimeTage
g3deftimeTage.description: The number of timeticks since the definity time data was last extracted from the switch by the Proxy Agent. This object along with the g3deftimeintvl object allows the Network Manager to determine the validity of the definity time data in the cache and to control when the Proxy Agent extracts the data from the switch.

g3deftimeTintvl.name: g3deftimeTintvl
g3deftimeTintvl.description: An object containing the interval for which the definity time data extracted from the switch is considered valid by the Proxy Agent. When a GET or GET-NEXT request for definity time objects is received by the agent it uses the g3deftimeage and g3deftimeintvl objects to determine whether it should refresh the cached deftimeTable. If g3deftimestmp + g3deftimeintvl is less than the current value of the sysUpTime object then the agent refreshes the deftimeTable cache. In either case it responds to the requests it receives with the data it currently has in the cache.

g3deftimeTdelay.name: g3deftimeTdelay
g3deftimeTdelay.description: An object containing the delay encountered in updating the cached data.

g3deftimeTretrieve.name: g3deftimeTretrieve

g3ipcodecsumTage.description: The number of timeticks since the ip codec summary data was last extracted from the switch by the Proxy Agent. This object along with the g3ipcodecsumintvl object allows the Network Manager to determine the validity of the ip codec summary data in the cache and to control when the Proxy Agent extracts the data from the switch.

g3ipcodecsumTintvl.name: g3ipcodecsumTintvl
g3ipcodecsumTintvl.description: An object containing the interval for which the data extracted from the switch is considered valid by the Proxy Agent. When a GET or GET-NEXT request for the ip codec summary objects is received by the agent it uses the g3ipcodecsumage and g3ipcodecsumintvl objects to determine whether it should refresh the cached ipcodecsumTable. If g3ipcodecsumstmp + g3ipcodecsumintvl is less than the current value of the sysUpTime object then the agent refreshes the ipcodecsumTable cache. In either case it responds to the requests it receives with the data it currently has in the cache.

g3regipstatTage.name: g3regipstatTage
g3regipstatTage.description: The number of timeticks since the registered ip stations data was last extracted from the switch by the Proxy Agent. This object along with the g3regipstatintvl object allows the Network Manager to determine the validity of the registered ip stations data in the cache and to control when the Proxy Agent extracts the data from the switch.

g3regipstatTintvl.name: g3regipstatTintvl
g3regipstatTintvl.description: An object containing the interval for which the data extracted from the switch is considered valid by the Proxy Agent. When a GET or GET-NEXT request for these registered ip stations data objects is received by the agent it uses the g3regipstatage and g3regipstatintvl objects to determine whether it should refresh the cached regipstatTable. If g3regipstatstmp + g3regipstatintvl is less than the current value of the sysUpTime object then the agent refreshes the regipstatTable cache. In either case it responds to the requests it receives with the data it currently has in the cache.

g3regipstatTdelay.name: g3regipstatTdelay
g3regipstatTdelay.description: An object containing the delay encountered in updating the cached data.

g3regipstatTretrieve.name: g3regipstatTretrieve
g3regipstatTretrieve.description: An object containing a flag that is 'update' if the cached data is being retrieved and otherwise 'current'. This object may be set to 'update' to force a refresh of the cache.

g3regipstatTcount.name: g3regipstatTcount
g3regipstatTcount.description: A Gauge object containing the number of data records in the cache.

g3regipstatEntry.name: g3regipstatEntry
g3regipstatEntry.description: A g3regipstat entry containing objects of the g3regipstat information sent by the switch.

g3regipstatExtension.name: g3regipstatExtension
g3regipstatExtension.description: An object containing the registered IP station extension. This MIB group is currently disabled in providing this data due to performance problems in running the associated CM SAT command.

When a GET or GET-NEXT request for these clan ppp data objects is received by the agent it uses the g3clanpppTage and g3clanpppTintvl objects to determine whether it should refresh the cached clanpppTable. If g3clanpppTstmp + g3clanpppTintvl is less than the current value of the sysUpTime object then the agent refreshes the clanpppTable cache.In either case it responds to the requests it receives with the data it currently has in the cache.

g3mmisumAvailableUsage.description: An object containing the total time that is available in the system for network MMI ports (in CCS units).

g3mmisumTotalUsage.name: g3mmisumTotalUsage
g3mmisumTotalUsage.description: An object containing the total time, in CCS units, that MMI ports are in use on a call. It includes the time that the ports are out of service or maintenance busy. Usage is measured from the time the port is allocated until it is released.

g3mmisumTotalAllocation.name: g3mmisumTotalAllocation
g3mmisumTotalAllocation.description: An object containing the total number of times that an MMI port was allocated to a call. Keep in mind that a 2-channel call occupies 2 ports, so this number does not necessarily reflect the number of calls that took place. Point-to-point calls do not use MMI resources, so these allocations are for conversion calls of multimedia conferences.

g3mmisumMMIDenials.name: g3mmisumMMIDenials
g3mmisumMMIDenials.description: An object containing the total number of times an MMI port was needed but could not be allocated because all ports were busy.

g3mmisumOutofService.name: g3mmisumOutofService
g3mmisumOutofService.description: An object containing the total time, in CCS units, that any MMI ports were out of service during any part of the measured interval.

g3mmisumPercentAPB.name: g3mmisumPercentAPB
g3mmisumPercentAPB.description: An object containing the percentage of time during the measured interval that all MMI ports are unavailable to carry a new call.

g3mmisumPercentBlock.name: g3mmisumPercentBlock
g3mmisumPercentBlock.description: An object containing the percentage of attempted allocations of MMI ports that are not successful (calculated as percent blockage = (MMI Denials/(Total Alloc + MMI Denials)) * 100).

g3pkvoicesumVoiceUsage.description: An object containing the total time that VC ports are allocated to voice endpoints.

g3pkvoicesumTotalUsage.name: g3pkvoicesumTotalUsage
g3pkvoicesumTotalUsage.description: An object containing the total time, in CCS units, that VC ports are unavailable to carry a new call. This includes time that the ports are busy on a call, out or service, or maintenance busy. Measured from the time that the port is allocated until it is released.

g3pkvoicesumH320Allocation.name: g3pkvoicesumH320Allocation
g3pkvoicesumH320Allocation.description: An object containing the total number of times a VC port was allocated to a H320 call.

g3pkvoicesumVoiceAllocation.name: g3pkvoicesumVoiceAllocation
g3pkvoicesumVoiceAllocation.description: An object containing the total number of times a VC port was allocated to a voice call.

g3pkvoicesumTotalAllocation.name: g3pkvoicesumTotalAllocation
g3pkvoicesumTotalAllocation.description: An object containing the total number of times a VC port was allocated to any call. Each B-channel used on a multimedia call counts as one allocation.

g3pkvoicesumH320Denials.name: g3pkvoicesumH320Denials
g3pkvoicesumH320Denials.description: An object containing the number of times a port was needed for an H320 call, but was not available.

g3pkvoicesumVoiceDenials.name: g3pkvoicesumVoiceDenials
g3pkvoicesumVoiceDenials.description: An object containing the number of times a port was need for a voice call, but was not available.

g3pkvoicesumTotalDenials.name: g3pkvoicesumTotalDenials
g3pkvoicesumTotalDenials.description: An object containing the total number of times a VC port was needed for any call, but was not allocated because all VC ports were busy.

g3pkvoicesumOutofService.name: g3pkvoicesumOutofService
g3pkvoicesumOutofService.description: An object containing the total time, in CCS units, that any VC ports were out of service during any part of the measured interval.

g3pkvoicesumPercentAPB.name: g3pkvoicesumPercentAPB

g3pkvoicesumPercentBlock.name: g3pkvoicesumPercentBlock
g3pkvoicesumPercentBlock.description: An object containing the percentage of attempted allocations of VC ports that are not successful. This value is calculated as percent blockage = ((Total VC Denials / (Total Alloc + Total VC Denials)) * 100).

When a GET or GET-NEXT request for the data is received by the agent it uses the g3principalTage and g3principalTintvl objects to determine whether it should refresh the data.

g3pkprincipalTdelay.name: g3pkprincipalTdelay
g3pkprincipalTdelay.description: An object containing the delay encountered in updating the cached data.

g3pkprincipalTretrieve.name: g3pkprincipalTretrieve
g3pkprincipalTretrieve.description: An object containing a flag that is 'update' if the cached data is being retrieved and otherwise 'current'.This object may be set to 'update' to force a refresh of the cache.

g3pkprincipalTcount.name: g3pkprincipalTcount
g3pkprincipalTcount.description: A Gauge object containing the number of data records in the cache.

g3pkprincipalEntry.name: g3pkprincipalEntry
g3pkprincipalEntry.description: A g3pkprincipal entry containing objects of the g3pkprincipal information sent by the switch.

g3pkprincipalExtensionTAC.name: g3pkprincipalExtensionTAC
g3pkprincipalExtensionTAC.description: An object containing the measured coverage path.

g3pkprincipalMeasHour.name: g3pkprincipalMeasHour
g3pkprincipalMeasHour.description: An object containing the starting time of the hour during which the greatest number of calls are offered to the principal.

g3pkprincipalCallsOffTotal.name: g3pkprincipalCallsOffTotal
g3pkprincipalCallsOffTotal.description: An object containing the number of calls offered to the principal. path.

g3pkprincipalCallsAband.name: g3pkprincipalCallsAband
g3pkprincipalCallsAband.description: An object containing the total number of abandoned calls, where the calling party hung up before the call was answered or sent to coverage.

g3pkprincipalCallsRedirect.name: g3pkprincipalCallsRedirect
g3pkprincipalCallsRedirect.description: An object containing the total number of calls not answered by the principal and subsequently sent to coverage.

g3pkprincipalCallsCAC.name: g3pkprincipalCallsCAC
g3pkprincipalCallsCAC.description: An object containing the number of calls sent to coverage by this principal due to the principal being active.

g3pkprincipalCallsCBC.name: g3pkprincipalCallsCBC
g3pkprincipalCallsCBC.description: An object containing the number of calls to coverage by this principal due to the principal being busy.

g3pkprincipalCallsCDAC.name: g3pkprincipalCallsCDAC
g3pkprincipalCallsCDAC.description: An object containing the number of calls sent to coverage by this principal because the principal didn't answer the call after the administered number of rings.

g3pkprincipalCallsCCAC.name: g3pkprincipalCallsCCAC
g3pkprincipalCallsCCAC.description: An object containing the number of calls sent to coverage by this principal due to the principal's use of Cover All.

g3pkprincipalCallsCSAC.name: g3pkprincipalCallsCSAC
g3pkprincipalCallsCSAC.description: An object containing the number of calls sent to coverage by this principal due to the principal's use of Send All Calls, or because the calling party used the Go To Cover feature.

g3pkprincipalCallsCSCB.name: g3pkprincipalCallsCSCB
g3pkprincipalCallsCSCB.description: An object containing the number of calls offered to this principal where the calling party used LWC or ACB before the principal answered the call and before it went to coverage.

g3pkprincipalCovPath1.name: g3pkprincipalCovPath1
g3pkprincipalCovPath1.description: An object containing a coverage path used by this principal.

g3pkprincipalCovPath2.name: g3pkprincipalCovPath2
g3pkprincipalCovPath2.description: An object containing a coverage path used by this principal.

g3pkprincipalCovPath3.name: g3pkprincipalCovPath3
g3pkprincipalCovPath3.description: An object containing a coverage path used by this principal.

g3pkprincipalCovPath4.name: g3pkprincipalCovPath4
g3pkprincipalCovPath4.description: An object containing a coverage path used by this principal.

g3pkprincipalCovPath5.name: g3pkprincipalCovPath5
g3pkprincipalCovPath5.description: An object containing a coverage path used by this principal.

g3pkprincipalCovPath6.name: g3pkprincipalCovPath6
g3pkprincipalCovPath6.description: An object containing a coverage path used by this principal.

g3pkprincipalCovPath7.name: g3pkprincipalCovPath7
g3pkprincipalCovPath7.description: An object containing a coverage path used by this principal.

g3pkprincipalCovPath8.name: g3pkprincipalCovPath8
g3pkprincipalCovPath8.description: An object containing a coverage path used by this principal.

g3esmainTage.name: g3esmainTage
g3esmainTage.description: The number of timeticks since the coverage path data was last extracted from the switch by the Proxy Agent. This object along with the g3esmainTintvl object allows the Network Manager to determine the validity of the data in the cache and to control when the Proxy Agent extracts the data from the switch.

g3esmainTintvl.name: g3esmainTintvl
g3esmainTintvl.description: An object containing the interval for which the data extracted from the switch is considered valid by the Proxy Agent. When a GET or GET-NEXT request for the data is received by the agent it uses the g3esmainTage and g3esmainTintvl objects to determine whether it should refresh the data.

g3esmainTdelay.name: g3esmainTdelay
g3esmainTdelay.description: An object containing the delay encountered in updating the cached data.

g3esmainTretrieve.name: g3esmainTretrieve
g3esmainTretrieve.description: An object containing a flag that is 'update' if the cached data is being retrieved and otherwise 'current'.This object may be set to 'update' to force a refresh of the cache.

g3esmainTcount.name: g3esmainTcount
g3esmainTcount.description: A Gauge object containing the number of data records in the cache.

g3esmainEntry.name: g3esmainEntry
g3esmainEntry.description: A g3esmain entry containing objects of the g3esmain information sent by the switch.

g3esmainClusterId.name: g3esmainClusterId
g3esmainClusterId.description: An object containing the unique module id, for the main server, from the license file for this cluster.

g3esmainPlatformType.name: g3esmainPlatformType
g3esmainPlatformType.description: An object containing the platform type (S8500 or S8700).

g3esmainServerAId.name: g3esmainServerAId
g3esmainServerAId.description: An object containing the Server A id field. Acceptable values are 1-999 and it must be unique.

g3esmainServerAIP1.name: g3esmainServerAIP1
g3esmainServerAIP1.description: An object containing the first part of the IP Address for Server A.

g3esmainServerAIP2.name: g3esmainServerAIP2
g3esmainServerAIP2.description: An object containing the second part of the IP Address for Server A.

g3esmainServerAIP3.name: g3esmainServerAIP3
g3esmainServerAIP3.description: An object containing the third part of the IP Address for Server A.

g3esmainServerAIP4.name: g3esmainServerAIP4
g3esmainServerAIP4.description: An object containing the last part of the IP Address for Server A.

g3esmainServerBId.name: g3esmainServerBId
g3esmainServerBId.description: An object containing the Server B id field. Acceptable values are 1-999 and it must be unique (only available if the platform type is S8700).

g3esmainServerBIP1.name: g3esmainServerBIP1
g3esmainServerBIP1.description: An object containing the first part of the IP Address for Server B.

g3esmainServerBIP2.name: g3esmainServerBIP2
g3esmainServerBIP2.description: An object containing the second part of the IP Address for Server B.

g3esmainServerBIP3.name: g3esmainServerBIP3
g3esmainServerBIP3.description: An object containing the third part of the IP Address for Server B.

g3esmainServerBIP4.name: g3esmainServerBIP4
g3esmainServerBIP4.description: An object containing the last part of the IP Address for Server B.

g3esmainPriorityScore.name: g3esmainPriorityScore
g3esmainPriorityScore.description: An object containing a numerical value that allows the customer to assign a preferred cluster (can accept values of 1-100; default is blank).

g3esmainNetComm.name: g3esmainNetComm
g3esmainNetComm.description: An object containing the region the ESS cluster is in (used for localization; can have values between 1-64; default is 1).

g3esmainSystemPref.name: g3esmainSystemPref
g3esmainSystemPref.description: An object containing a flag that provides the cluster with a weighting factor that makes it a candidate to provide service on a system-wide basis (values can be 'y' or 'n'; default is 'y').

g3esmainLocalPref.name: g3esmainLocalPref
g3esmainLocalPref.description: An object containing a flag that provides the cluster with a weighting factor that makes it a candidate to provide service in the same network community before clusters in other network communities would be selected (values can be 'y' or 'n'; default is 'n').

g3esmainLocalOnly.name: g3esmainLocalOnly
g3esmainLocalOnly.description: An object containing a flag indicating that only clusters in the same network community can provide service (values can be 'y' or 'n'; default is 'n').

g3esserversTage.name: g3esserversTage
g3esserversTage.description: The number of timeticks since the coverage path data was last extracted from the switch by the Proxy Agent. This object along with the g3esserversTintvl object allows the Network Manager to determine the validity of the data in the cache and to control when the Proxy Agent extracts the data from the switch.

g3esserversTintvl.name: g3esserversTintvl
g3esserversTintvl.description: An object containing the interval for which the data extracted from the switch is considered valid by the Proxy Agent. When a GET or GET-NEXT request for the data is received by the agent it uses the g3esserversTage and g3esserversTintvl objects to determine whether it should refresh the data.

g3esserversTdelay.name: g3esserversTdelay
g3esserversTdelay.description: An object containing the delay encountered in updating the cached data.

g3esserversTretrieve.name: g3esserversTretrieve
g3esserversTretrieve.description: An object containing a flag that is 'update' if the cached data is being retrieved and otherwise 'current'.This object may be set to 'update' to force a refresh of the cache.

g3esserversTcount.name: g3esserversTcount
g3esserversTcount.description: A Gauge object containing the number of data records in the cache.

g3esserversEntry.name: g3esserversEntry
g3esserversEntry.description: A g3esservers entry containing objects of the g3esservers information sent by the switch.

g3esserversClusterId.name: g3esserversClusterId
g3esserversClusterId.description: An object containing the unique module id, for the enterprise survivable server, from the license file for this cluster.

g3esserversPlatformType.name: g3esserversPlatformType
g3esserversPlatformType.description: An object containing the platform type (S8500 or S8700).

g3esserversServerAId.name: g3esserversServerAId
g3esserversServerAId.description: An object containing the Server A id field. Acceptable values are 1-999 and it must be unique.

g3esserversServerAIP1.name: g3esserversServerAIP1
g3esserversServerAIP1.description: An object containing the first part of the IP Address for Server A. This field is now obsolete. The g3esserversServerANodeName field replaces the IP address.

g3esserversServerAIP2.name: g3esserversServerAIP2
g3esserversServerAIP2.description: An object containing the second part of the IP Address for Server A. This field is now obsolete. The g3esserversServerANodeName field replaces the IP address.

g3esserversServerAIP3.name: g3esserversServerAIP3
g3esserversServerAIP3.description: An object containing the third part of the IP Address for Server A. This field is now obsolete. The g3esserversServerANodeName field replaces the IP address.

g3esserversServerAIP4.name: g3esserversServerAIP4
g3esserversServerAIP4.description: An object containing the last part of the IP Address for Server A. This field is now obsolete. The g3esserversServerANodeName field replaces the IP address.

g3esserversServerBId.name: g3esserversServerBId
g3esserversServerBId.description: An object containing the Server B id field. Acceptable values are 1-999 and it must be unique (only available if the platform type is S8700).

g3esserversServerBIP1.name: g3esserversServerBIP1
g3esserversServerBIP1.description: An object containing the first part of the IP Address for Server B. This field is now obsolete. The g3esserversServerBNodeName field replaces the IP address.

g3esserversServerBIP2.name: g3esserversServerBIP2
g3esserversServerBIP2.description: An object containing the second part of the IP Address for Server B. This field is now obsolete. The g3esserversServerBNodeName field replaces the IP address.

g3esserversServerBIP3.name: g3esserversServerBIP3
g3esserversServerBIP3.description: An object containing the third part of the IP Address for Server B. This field is now obsolete. The g3esserversServerBNodeName field replaces the IP address.

g3esserversServerBIP4.name: g3esserversServerBIP4
g3esserversServerBIP4.description: An object containing the last part of the IP Address for Server B. This field is now obsolete. The g3esserversServerBNodeName field replaces the IP address.

g3esserversPriorityScore.name: g3esserversPriorityScore
g3esserversPriorityScore.description: An object containing a numerical value that allows the customer to assign a preferred cluster (can accept values of 1-100; default is blank).

g3esserversNetComm.name: g3esserversNetComm
g3esserversNetComm.description: An object containing the region the ESS cluster is in (used for localization; can have values between 1-64; default is 1).

g3esserversSystemPref.name: g3esserversSystemPref
g3esserversSystemPref.description: An object containing a flag that provides the cluster with a weighting factor that makes it a candidate to provide service on a system-wide basis (values can be 'y' or 'n'; default is 'y').

g3esserversLocalPref.name: g3esserversLocalPref
g3esserversLocalPref.description: An object containing a flag that provides the cluster with a weighting factor that makes it a candidate to provide service in the same network community before clusters in other network communities would be selected (values can be 'y' or 'n'; default is 'n').

g3esserversLocalOnly.name: g3esserversLocalOnly
g3esserversLocalOnly.description: An object containing a flag indicating that only clusters in the same network community can provide service (values can be 'y' or 'n'; default is 'n').

g3esserversServerANodeName.name: g3esserversServerANodeName
g3esserversServerANodeName.description: An object containing the node name of Server A.

g3esserversServerBNodeName.name: g3esserversServerBNodeName
g3esserversServerBNodeName.description: An object containing the node name of Server B.

g3esparmsTage.name: g3esparmsTage
g3esparmsTage.description: The number of timeticks since the coverage path data was last extracted from the switch by the Proxy Agent. This object along with the g3esparmsTintvl object allows the Network Manager to determine the validity of the data in the cache and to control when the Proxy Agent extracts the data from the switch.

g3esparmsTintvl.name: g3esparmsTintvl
g3esparmsTintvl.description: An object containing the interval for which the data extracted from the switch is considered valid by the Proxy Agent. When a GET or GET-NEXT request for the data is received by the agent it uses the g3esparmsTage and g3esparmsTintvl objects to determine whether it should refresh the data.

g3esparmsTdelay.name: g3esparmsTdelay
g3esparmsTdelay.description: An object containing the delay encountered in updating the cached data.

g3esparmsTretrieve.name: g3esparmsTretrieve
g3esparmsTretrieve.description: An object containing a flag that is 'update' if the cached data is being retrieved and otherwise 'current'.This object may be set to 'update' to force a refresh of the cache.

g3esparmsTcount.name: g3esparmsTcount
g3esparmsTcount.description: A Gauge object containing the number of data records in the cache.

g3esparmsNetCommunity1.name: g3esparmsNetCommunity1
g3esparmsNetCommunity1.description: An object containing a network community value for the corresponding port network (can have values between 1-64; default is 1).

g3esparmsAutoReturn.name: g3esparmsAutoReturn
g3esparmsAutoReturn.description: An object containing the state of auto return (values can be 'y' (yes), 'n' (no), or 's' (scheduled); default is 'n').

g3esparmsDay.name: g3esparmsDay
g3esparmsDay.description: An object containing the day of the week Saturday through Sunday (or every day) on which the auto return will occur (only applicable if AutoReturn is set to scheduled).

g3esparmsHour.name: g3esparmsHour
g3esparmsHour.description: An object containing the hour of the day (0-23) at which the auto return will occur (only applicable if AutoReturn is set to scheduled).

g3esparmsMinute.name: g3esparmsMinute
g3esparmsMinute.description: An object containing the minute of the hour (0-59) at which the auto return will occur (only applicable if AutoReturn is set to scheduled).

g3esparmsNoServerTO.name: g3esparmsNoServerTO
g3esparmsNoServerTO.description: An object containing a no service timeout interval indicating when the fail over will occur (can have values between 3-15 minutes; default is 5 minutes).

g3esparmsIPSIConnUp.name: g3esparmsIPSIConnUp
g3esparmsIPSIConnUp.description: An object containing the number of minutes that an IPSI in a Port Network has a connection to the Main server and the Port Network is available for auto-return (can have values between 3-120 or blank if the g3esparmsAutoReturn field is not set to 'y').

g3mgrecruleTage.name: g3mgrecruleTage
g3mgrecruleTage.description: The number of timeticks since the coverage path data was last extracted from the switch by the Proxy Agent. This object along with the g3mgrecruleTintvl object allows the Network Manager to determine the validity of the data in the cache and to control when the Proxy Agent extracts the data from the switch.

g3mgrecruleTintvl.name: g3mgrecruleTintvl
g3mgrecruleTintvl.description: An object containing the interval for which the data extracted from the switch is considered valid by the Proxy Agent. When a GET or GET-NEXT request for the data is received by the agent it uses the g3mgrecruleTage and g3mgrecruleTintvl objects to determine whether it should refresh the data.

g3mgrecruleTdelay.name: g3mgrecruleTdelay
g3mgrecruleTdelay.description: An object containing the delay encountered in updating the cached data.

g3mgrecruleTretrieve.name: g3mgrecruleTretrieve
g3mgrecruleTretrieve.description: An object containing a flag that is 'update' if the cached data is being retrieved and otherwise 'current'.This object may be set to 'update' to force a refresh of the cache.

g3mgrecruleTcount.name: g3mgrecruleTcount
g3mgrecruleTcount.description: A Gauge object containing the number of data records in the cache.

g3mgrecruleEntry.name: g3mgrecruleEntry
g3mgrecruleEntry.description: A g3mgrecrule entry containing objects of the g3mgrecrule information sent by the switch.

g3mgrecruleGatewayNbr.name: g3mgrecruleGatewayNbr
g3mgrecruleGatewayNbr.description: An object containing the media gateway number (1-250).

g3mgrecruleGatewayName.name: g3mgrecruleGatewayName
g3mgrecruleGatewayName.description: An object containing the name of the media gateway.

g3mgrecruleRecRule.name: g3mgrecruleRecRule
g3mgrecruleRecRule.description: An object containing the recovery rule type that has been selected for the media gateway (possible values are 'immediately', '0-active-calls', 'time-day-window', or 'time-window-OR-0-active-calls'.

g3commprocTage.name: g3commprocTage
g3commprocTage.description: The number of timeticks since the processor channel data was last extracted from the switch by the Proxy Agent. This object along with the g3commprocTintvl object allows the Network Manager to determine the validity of the data in the cache and to control when the agent extracts the data from the switch.

g3commprocTintvl.name: g3commprocTintvl
g3commprocTintvl.description: An object containing the interval for which the data extracted from the switch is considered valid by the agent. When a GET or GET-NEXT request for the data is received by the agent it uses the g3commprocTage and g3commprocTintvl objects to determine whether it should refresh the data.

g3commprocTdelay.name: g3commprocTdelay
g3commprocTdelay.description: An object containing the delay encountered in updating the cached data.

g3commprocTretrieve.name: g3commprocTretrieve
g3commprocTretrieve.description: An object containing a flag that is 'update' if the cached data is being retrieved and otherwise 'current'.This object may be set to 'update' to force a refresh of the cache.

g3commprocTcount.name: g3commprocTcount
g3commprocTcount.description: A Gauge object containing the number of data records in the cache.

g3commprocEntry.name: g3commprocEntry
g3commprocEntry.description: A g3commproc entry containing objects of the g3commproc information sent by the switch.

g3commprocProcChan.name: g3commprocProcChan
g3commprocProcChan.description: An object containing the processor channel (1-384).

g3commprocEnable.name: g3commprocEnable
g3commprocEnable.description: An object containing whether the processor channel is enabled (y or n).

g3commprocApplication.name: g3commprocApplication
g3commprocApplication.description: An object containing the application type or adjunct connection used on the channel. Allowed values are 'audix', 'dcs', 'echo', 'fp-mwi', 'gateway', 'mis', and 'qsig-mwi'.

g3commprocGatewayTo.name: g3commprocGatewayTo
g3commprocGatewayTo.description: An object identifying which processor channel the specific processor channel is serving as a gateway to (1-384 or blank).

g3commprocMode.name: g3commprocMode
g3commprocMode.description: An object specifying the mode of the IP session (values include 'c' for client, 's' for server, or blank).

g3commprocInterfaceLink.name: g3commprocInterfaceLink
g3commprocInterfaceLink.description: An object that identifies the physical link carrying the processor channel (values include 1-99, 'p' for processor, or blank).

g3commprocInterfaceChan.name: g3commprocInterfaceChan
g3commprocInterfaceChan.description: An object that identifies the channel number of the TCP/IP listen port channel to carry the processor channel (values 1-64 for link type x.25, 0 or 5000-64500 for ethernet or ppp with 0 meaning any port can be used).

g3commprocDestNode.name: g3commprocDestNode
g3commprocDestNode.description: An object that identifies the server or adjunct at the far end of the link (values include either an adjunct name, server name, far end IP address, node name, or blank for local services).

g3commprocTempA.name: g3commprocTempA
g3commprocTempA.description: An object internally used by the agent for data storage (will always return blank).

g3commprocTempB.name: g3commprocTempB
g3commprocTempB.description: An object internally used by the agent for data storage (will always return blank).

g3commprocDestPort.name: g3commprocDestPort
g3commprocDestPort.description: An object that identifies the port number of the destination (values 0 or 5000-64500 where 0 meaning any port can be used).

g3commprocSessionLocal.name: g3commprocSessionLocal
g3commprocSessionLocal.description: An object that specifies the local session number (1-384 or blank).

g3commprocSessionRemote.name: g3commprocSessionRemote
g3commprocSessionRemote.description: An object that specifies the remote session number (1-384 or blank).

g3commprocMachID.name: g3commprocMachID
g3commprocMachID.description: An object that identifies the destination server ID defined on the dial plan of the destination server (values 1-99 or blank).

g3busyrlsAction.name: g3busyrlsAction
g3busyrlsAction.description: The last action performed on a specified object. This field must be set in conjunction with the g3busyrlsObject field.

g3busyrlsObject.name: g3busyrlsObject
g3busyrlsObject.description: The object associated with the last action. This field must be set in conjunction with the g3busyrlsTrunkGroup, g3busyrlsTrunkMember, g3busyrlsBoard, and g3busyrlsPort fields. This field can only be set to 'media-processor' if g3busyrlsAction is either 'campon-busyout' or 'release'.

g3busyrlsTrunkGroup.name: g3busyrlsTrunkGroup
g3busyrlsTrunkGroup.description: The trunk group number associated with the g3busyrlsObject field. This field is only applicable if the g3busyrlsObject field is set to 'trunk'.

g3busyrlsTrunkMember.name: g3busyrlsTrunkMember
g3busyrlsTrunkMember.description: The trunk group member associated with the g3busyrlsObject field. This field is only applicable if the g3busyrlsObject field is set to 'trunk'. This field either contains a trunk member number (1-255) or a '0' if an entire trunk group (all members) is to be operated on by the last action.

g3busyrlsBoard.name: g3busyrlsBoard
g3busyrlsBoard.description: A DisplayString that uniquely identifies a board location (cabinet(01-22):carrier(A-E):slot(01-20)) associated with the g3busyrlsObject field. This field is only applicable if the g3busyrlsObject field is set to 'board' or 'media-processor'.

g3busyrlsPort.name: g3busyrlsPort
g3busyrlsPort.description: The port location associated with the g3busyrlsObject field. This field is only applicable if the g3busyrlsObject field is set to 'board'. This field either contains a port location number (1-24) or a '0' if an entire board (all ports on the board) are to be operated on by the last action.

g3clientEntry.name: g3clientEntry
g3clientEntry.description: A g3client entry containing objects of the g3client information for the G3 Proxy Agent.

g3clientCommunity.name: g3clientCommunity
g3clientCommunity.description: A DisplayString Object containing the Community substring for a G3 client.

g3clientCustomerId.name: g3clientCustomerId
g3clientCustomerId.description: A DisplayString Object containing the Customer ID for a G3 client.

g3clientDescription.name: g3clientDescription
g3clientDescription.description: A DisplayString Object containing the Description for a G3 client.

g3clientExternalName.name: g3clientExternalName
g3clientExternalName.description: A DisplayString Object containing the External Name for a G3 client.

g3clientConnectStatus.name: g3clientConnectStatus
g3clientConnectStatus.description: A DisplayString Object containing the Connection Status for a G3 client.

g3clientSubmapType.name: g3clientSubmapType
g3clientSubmapType.description: The type of submap on which the managed node icon is to be placed on the NMS ('generic' = '0', 'usa' = '1', and 'custom' = '2').

g3clientState.name: g3clientState
g3clientState.description: An INTEGER object containing a numeric value representing the state in which to place the managed node icon on the NMS if the g3connectSubmapType is set to 'usa' ('Alabama' = '0', 'Alaska' = 1, . . . 'Wyoming' = 49).

g3clientSubmapName.name: g3clientSubmapName
g3clientSubmapName.description: A DisplayString Object containing the submap name in which to place the managed node icon on the NMS if g3clientSubmapType is set to 'custom'.

g3clientConnectType.name: g3clientConnectType
g3clientConnectType.description: A DisplayString Object containing the Connection Type for a G3 client.

g3clientDynamicTimeout.name: g3clientDynamicTimeout
g3clientDynamicTimeout.description: An INTEGER object containing the number of idle minutes to wait before a dynamic connection is dropped.

g3clientEnumType.name: g3clientEnumType
g3clientEnumType.description: The enumerated type of submap on which the managed node icon is to be placed on the NMS.

g3clientEnumState.name: g3clientEnumState
g3clientEnumState.description: An INTEGER object containing an enumerated value of the state in which to place the managed node icon on the NMS if the g3connectEnumType is set to 'usa'.

g3clientDialString1.name: g3clientDialString1
g3clientDialString1.description: A DisplayString Object containing the first dial string administered for the managed node.

g3clientDialString2.name: g3clientDialString2
g3clientDialString2.description: A DisplayString Object containing the second dial string administered for the managed node.

g3clientProductID.name: g3clientProductID
g3clientProductID.description: A DisplayString Object containing the product ID of the managed node.

g3clientTableIndex.name: g3clientTableIndex

g3trapXReboot.name: g3trapXReboot

g3trapInterchange.name: g3trapInterchange
g3trapInterchange.description: This field indicates whether or not only restarts involving a interchange are to have traps generated. It can take on the values 'y' (only restarts involving an interchange are trapped), 'n' (only restarts involving no interchange are trapped), or '-' (don't care - in other words restarts are trapped regardless of whether an interchange occurred or not). It is defaulted to '-'. This field only applies to system restart notifications.

g3trapCraftInitiated.name: g3trapCraftInitiated
g3trapCraftInitiated.description: This field indicates whether or not restarts that are craft initiated are to have traps generated. It can take on the vaules 'y' (only craft initiated restarts are trapped), 'n' (only restarts that are not craft initiated are trapped), or '-' (don't care - in other workds restarts are trapped regardless of whether they were craft initiated or not). It is defaulted to '-'. This field only applies to system restart notifications.

g3trapFilterType.name: g3trapFilterType
g3trapFilterType.description: This field indicates the type of the filter. It is defaulted to a value of 'cm-alarm' if the user does not specify a filter type when adding a new filter.

g3filterFilterStatus.name: g3filterFilterStatus
g3filterFilterStatus.description: This field indicates the state of alarm trap filter table. A value of 'current' indicates that the set of alarm filters are up-to-date and active and that no filter updates, via the g3trap MIB group are currently taking place. A value of 'update' means that filter updates are taking place via SNMP sets of the g3trap MIB group variables. The rest of the values are settable by the user. When doing an SNMP set on this MIB variable the g3filterApplication field must also be set to indicate what application is requesting the set operation. For more details on that field a full description is provided further down in the MIB table. A value of 'abort' will cancelled any filter updates in progress and return the filter table to its original state before updates began. A value of 'save' will commit all pending filter updates and the new/modified set of filters will become active. A value of 'clear' will remove all active filters from the filter table for the specified application ID. A value of 'off' will turn off the alarm trap handling processes, abort any filter updates in process, but will continue to store the current set of active filters. It's value will display when an SNMP get request is made if the user had previously set the filter status to that value or if alarm trap handling is on but no active filters exist. A value of 'on' will reactivate the alarm trap handling processes using the currently stored set of active filters (by default the alarm trap handling processes turned on at agent startup if any active filters exist).
